@prefix drift: <https://w3id.org/word-drift/ontology#> .
@prefix rdfs:  <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

# =============================================================
# WORD-DRIFT — Module 07: Supplementary annotations
# Purely ADDITIVE human-readable annotations (rdfs:label /
# rdfs:comment) that close OOPS! pitfall P08 ("Missing
# annotations") on properties that previously carried a label
# but no descriptive comment, or vice versa. NO class/property
# axioms (domain, range, sub*Of, type) are touched here — this
# file changes documentation only, never semantics.
# See data/reports/oops-scan.md for the scan that motivated it.
# =============================================================

# --- frequency-observation link properties (had labels, no comments) ---
drift:ofWord
    rdfs:comment "Links a frequency observation to the word it measures."@en .

drift:ofSense
    rdfs:comment "Links a frequency observation to the specific sense it measures, when the count is sense-disambiguated rather than form-level."@en .

drift:observedYear
    rdfs:comment "Calendar year (xsd:gYear) for which a frequency observation reports its value."@en .

# --- drift-event link properties (had labels, no comments) ---
drift:affectsWord
    rdfs:comment "Links a drift event to the word whose meaning shifted."@en .

# --- causal-hypothesis link property (had label, no comment) ---
drift:aboutDrift
    rdfs:comment "Links a causal hypothesis to the drift event it tries to explain (ADR 0004)."@en .

# --- trigger-event classification property (had label, no comment) ---
drift:triggerCategory
    rdfs:comment "Classifies a trigger event by the kind of real-world event it is, drawn from drift:TriggerCategoryScheme (political, pandemic, technological, cultural, media, commercial)."@en .

# --- source property (had label, no comment) ---
drift:sourceURL
    rdfs:comment "Dereferenceable URL of the source (corpus query, dictionary entry, dataset record, or publication)."@en .
